{"title_page": "Isabella (The Sopranos)", "text_new": "{{Refimprove|date=November 2018}}\n{{DISPLAYTITLE:Isabella (''The Sopranos'')}}\n{{Infobox television episode\n| title          = Isabella\n| series         = [[The Sopranos]]\n| caption        = Tony's new neighbor Isabella.\n| season         = 1\n| episode        = 12\n| guests         = ''see below''\n| airdate        = March 28, 1999\n| length         = 47 minutes\n| editor         = \n| production     = 112\n| writer         = [[Robin Green]]<br />[[Mitchell Burgess]]\n| director       = [[Allen Coulter]]\n| photographer   = [[Phil Abraham]]\n| episode_list   = List of The Sopranos episodes\n| season_article = The Sopranos (season 1)\n| image          = Sopranos ep112.jpg\n| image_size     = 300px\n| prev           = [[Nobody Knows Anything]]\n| next           = [[I Dream of Jeannie Cusamano]]\n}}\n\"'''Isabella'''\" is the 12th episode of the [[HBO]] original series ''[[The Sopranos]]''. Written by [[Robin Green]] and [[Mitchell Burgess]], and directed by [[Allen Coulter]], it originally aired on March 28, 1999.\n\n==Starring==\n* [[James Gandolfini]] as [[Tony Soprano]]\n* [[Lorraine Bracco]] as [[Dr. Jennifer Melfi]]\n* [[Edie Falco]] as [[Carmela Soprano]]\n* [[Michael Imperioli]] as [[Christopher Moltisanti]]\n* [[Dominic Chianese]] as [[Junior Soprano|Corrado Soprano, Jr.]]\n* [[Vincent Pastore]] as [[Pussy Bonpensiero]] *\n* [[Steven Van Zandt]] as [[Silvio Dante]]\n* [[Tony Sirico]] as [[Paulie Gualtieri]]\n* [[Robert Iler]] as [[Anthony Soprano, Jr.]]\n* [[Jamie-Lynn Sigler]] as [[Meadow Soprano]]\n* [[Nancy Marchand]] as [[Livia Soprano]]\n\n''* = credit only''\n\n===Guest starring===\n{{Columns-list|colwidth=30em|\n* [[Maria Grazia Cucinotta]] as Isabella \n* [[Al Sapienza]] as [[Mikey Palmice]]\n* [[Paul Schulze]] as [[List of characters from The Sopranos - Friends and Family#Father Phil Intintola|Father Phil]]\n* [[Matt Servitto]] as [[Dwight Harris|Agent Harris]]\n* [[Joseph Badalucco Jr.|Joe Badalucco, Jr.]] as [[List of characters from The Sopranos in the Soprano crime family#Jimmy Altieri|Jimmy Altieri]]\n* John Eddins as [[List of characters from The Sopranos in the Soprano crime family#William \"Petite\" Clayborn|William \"Petite\" Clayborn]]\n* Touche as [[List of characters from The Sopranos in the Soprano crime family#Rasheen Ray|Rasheen Ray]]\n* Kareen Germaine as Nurse\n* Johnathan Mondel as Boy\n* Jack O'Connell as Vendor\n* Katalin Pota as Lilliana\n* Denise Richardson as Newscaster\n* Sal Ruffino as [[List of characters from The Sopranos in the Soprano crime family#Charles \"Chucky\" Signore|Chucky Signore]]\n* Bittu Walia as Doctor\n* [[David Wike]] as [[List of characters from The Sopranos in the Soprano crime family#Donnie Paduana|Donnie Paduana]]\n}}\n\n==Synopsis==\nFollowing his suspicion of [[Pussy Bonpensiero|Pussy]] and then his disappearance, [[Tony Soprano|Tony]] is deeply depressed and can hardly get out of bed. However, he sees a beautiful [[Italian people|Italian]] woman in the Cusamanos' garden next door. Her name is Isabella, she tells him; she is a [[Student exchange program|foreign exchange student]], staying there while the Cusamanos are away. He takes her out to lunch. As she describes the beauty of [[Avellino]], where Tony's grandfather came from, he has a daydream. Isabella is in a village house, in a rocking-chair, [[breastfeeding|nursing]] a baby named Antonio.\n\nThen Isabella is no longer there. When the Cusamanos return and he asks about her, Tony realizes she never existed: it was a [[hallucination|delusion]]. [[Jennifer Melfi|Dr. Melfi]] instructs him to cease taking [[Lithium pharmacology|lithium]], and theorizes that Isabella was an idealized maternal figure. \n\n[[Mikey Palmice|Mikey]], acting through [[List of characters from The Sopranos in the Soprano crime family#Donnie Paduana|Donnie Paduana]], has contracted two black gunmen to carry out the hit on Tony. When he tries to report the details to [[Junior Soprano|Junior]], he cannot bear to hear them, and stops him.   \n\nWhen Tony goes out on the day, [[Christopher Moltisanti|Chris]], who is concerned about his boss's emotional state, secretly follows him and  unknowingly prevents the hit when he pulls his car up next to the assassins'. There is an urgent outdoor meeting between Mikey and Donnie; Junior is present, hiding on the back seat of the car. Donnie promises the hit will be the next day, and casually remarks that even Tony's mother wants him dead. Junior, fearing the gossip, wordlessly tells Mikey to kill Donnie, and he does it. \n\nThe next day, the assassins make their move. In a ferocious struggle, one of them is killed and the other is briefly dragged along the street as Tony drives away. Elated, he can't help crashing into a parked car. In the hospital, with only minor injuries, he says it was an attempted carjack, but not even [[Anthony Soprano, Jr.|A.J.]] believes that. [[Federal Bureau of Investigation|FBI]] Agent [[Dwight Harris|Harris]] comes to his bed and offers a deal, including [[immunity from prosecution]], which Tony scornfully rejects.\n\nThe next day, Livia and Junior call on Tony at home. Livia apparently cannot recognize her granddaughter; Junior comments on the \"good timing\" of this memory loss.\n\n==Deceased==\n* '''[[List of characters from The Sopranos in the Soprano crime family#Donnie Paduana|Donnie Paduana]]:''' murdered by [[Mikey Palmice]] on orders of Uncle Junior.\n* '''[[List of characters from The Sopranos in the Soprano crime family#William \"Petite\" Clayborn|William \"Petite\" Clayborn]]:''' accidentally shot by his partner, Rasheen Ray, in the failed attempt on Tony Soprano's life.\n\n==Title reference==\nIsabella is the Italian exchange student Tony hallucinates.\n\n==Music==\n* The song played at the Bada Bing when Christopher and Silvio discuss Tony's depression is \"Ugly Stadium\" by Tipsy. \n* The song that is played twice during this episode (when Tony is in his bedroom, and again during the \"carjacking\") is \"Tiny Tears\" by [[Tindersticks]].\n* The song played as the would-be assassins are stalking Tony at the newsstand is \"Cry\" by [[Thornetta Davis]]\n* The song that is played briefly after Tony's meeting with Dr. Melfi, when he runs into Isabella, is \"Ballad of Tindersticks (instrumental)\" also by Tindersticks.\n* The song played when Tony and Isabella have lunch is \"Milonga del Angel\" by [[Al Di Meola]]. \n* The song played while Mikey kills Donnie Paduana is \"[[Temptation Waits]]\" by [[Garbage (band)|Garbage]].\n* The song played over the end credits is \"[[I Feel Free]]\" by [[Cream (band)|Cream]].\n\n== Filming locations ==\nListed in order of first appearance:<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.sopranos-locations.com/season-1/episode-12/|title=The Sopranos location guide - Filming locations for|last=Ugoku|website=www.sopranos-locations.com|language=en|access-date=2020-02-23}}</ref>\n\n* [[Belleville, New Jersey]]\n* [[Bada Bing!|Satin Dolls]] in [[Lodi, New Jersey]]\n* [[North Caldwell, New Jersey]]\n* [[Montclair, New Jersey]]\n* [[Greenpoint, Brooklyn]]\n* [[Van Vleck House and Gardens|Van Vleck House]] in Montclair, New Jersey\n* [[West Orange, New Jersey]]\n\n==Reception==\n[[Alan Sepinwall]] has lauded \"Isabella\" as one of the greatest episodes of ''The Sopranos''.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://uproxx.com/sepinwall/the-sopranos-rewind-season-1-episode-12-isabella/|title=In another 'Sopranos' classic, Tony has to fight off two assassins|date=2015-08-26|work=UPROXX|access-date=2018-04-09|language=en-US}}</ref> Emily VanDerWerff found the subplot with the titular character to be outlandish, but still described the episode as featuring \"classic scene after classic scene\".<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://tv.avclub.com/the-sopranos-isabella-i-dream-of-jeannie-cusamano-1798165529|title=The Sopranos: \"Isabella\"/\"I Dream of Jeannie Cusamano\"|last=VanDerWerff|first=Emily|work=TV Club|access-date=2018-04-09|language=en-US}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n<references />\n\n==External links==\n*[http://www.hbo.com/the-sopranos/episodes/index.html#/the-sopranos/episodes/1/12-isabella/index.html \"Isabella\"] at [[HBO]]\n*{{imdb episode|0705256|Isabella}}\n*{{tv.com episode|the-sopranos/isabella-26459|Isabella}}\n\n{{The Sopranos}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Isabella}}\n[[Category:The Sopranos (season 1) episodes]]\n[[Category:1999 American television episodes]]\n\n[[fr:Isabella (Les Soprano)]]\n", "text_old": "{{Refimprove|date=November 2018}}\n{{DISPLAYTITLE:Isabella (''The Sopranos'')}}\n{{Infobox television episode\n| title = Isabella\n| series = [[The Sopranos]]\n| season = 1\n| episode = 12\n| guests= ''see below''\n| airdate = March 28, 1999\n| length = 47 minutes\n| production = 112\n| writer = [[Robin Green]]<br />[[Mitchell Burgess]]\n| director = [[Allen Coulter]]\n| photographer = [[Phil Abraham]]\n| episode_list = List of The Sopranos episodes\n| season_article = The Sopranos (season 1)\n| image = Sopranos ep112.jpg\n| image_size = 300px\n| prev = [[Nobody Knows Anything]]\n| next = [[I Dream of Jeannie Cusamano]]\n}}\n\"'''Isabella'''\" is the 12th episode of the [[HBO]] original series ''[[The Sopranos]]''. Written by [[Robin Green]] and [[Mitchell Burgess]], and directed by [[Allen Coulter]], it originally aired on March 28, 1999.\n\n==Starring==\n* [[James Gandolfini]] as [[Tony Soprano]]\n* [[Lorraine Bracco]] as [[Dr. Jennifer Melfi]]\n* [[Edie Falco]] as [[Carmela Soprano]]\n* [[Michael Imperioli]] as [[Christopher Moltisanti]]\n* [[Dominic Chianese]] as [[Junior Soprano|Corrado Soprano, Jr.]]\n* [[Vincent Pastore]] as [[Pussy Bonpensiero]] *\n* [[Steven Van Zandt]] as [[Silvio Dante]]\n* [[Tony Sirico]] as [[Paulie Gualtieri]]\n* [[Robert Iler]] as [[Anthony Soprano, Jr.]]\n* [[Jamie-Lynn Sigler]] as [[Meadow Soprano]]\n* [[Nancy Marchand]] as [[Livia Soprano]]\n\n''* = credit only''\n\n===Guest starring===\n{{Columns-list|colwidth=30em|\n* [[Maria Grazia Cucinotta]] as Isabella \n* [[Al Sapienza]] as [[Mikey Palmice]]\n* [[Paul Schulze]] as [[List of characters from The Sopranos - Friends and Family#Father Phil Intintola|Father Phil]]\n* [[Matt Servitto]] as [[Dwight Harris|Agent Harris]]\n* [[Joseph Badalucco Jr.|Joe Badalucco, Jr.]] as [[List of characters from The Sopranos in the Soprano crime family#Jimmy Altieri|Jimmy Altieri]]\n* John Eddins as [[List of characters from The Sopranos in the Soprano crime family#William \"Petite\" Clayborn|William \"Petite\" Clayborn]]\n* Touche as [[List of characters from The Sopranos in the Soprano crime family#Rasheen Ray|Rasheen Ray]]\n* Kareen Germaine as Nurse\n* Johnathan Mondel as Boy\n* Jack O'Connell as Vendor\n* Katalin Pota as Lilliana\n* Denise Richardson as Newscaster\n* Sal Ruffino as [[List of characters from The Sopranos in the Soprano crime family#Charles \"Chucky\" Signore|Chucky Signore]]\n* Bittu Walia as Doctor\n* [[David Wike]] as [[List of characters from The Sopranos in the Soprano crime family#Donnie Paduana|Donnie Paduana]]\n}}\n\n==Synopsis==\nFollowing his suspicion of [[Pussy Bonpensiero|Pussy]] and then his disappearance, [[Tony Soprano|Tony]] is deeply depressed and can hardly get out of bed. However, he sees a beautiful [[Italian people|Italian]] woman in the Cusamanos' garden next door. Her name is Isabella, she tells him; she is a [[Student exchange program|foreign exchange student]], staying there while the Cusamanos are away. He takes her out to lunch. As she describes the beauty of [[Avellino]], where Tony's grandfather came from, he has a daydream. Isabella is in a village house, in a rocking-chair, [[breastfeeding|nursing]] a baby named Antonio.\n\nThen Isabella is no longer there. When the Cusamanos return and he asks about her, Tony realizes she never existed: it was a [[hallucination|delusion]]. [[Jennifer Melfi|Dr. Melfi]] instructs him to cease taking [[Lithium pharmacology|lithium]], and theorizes that Isabella was an idealized maternal figure. \n\n[[Mikey Palmice|Mikey]], acting through [[List of characters from The Sopranos in the Soprano crime family#Donnie Paduana|Donnie Paduana]], has contracted two black gunmen to carry out the hit on Tony. When he tries to report the details to [[Junior Soprano|Junior]], he cannot bear to hear them, and stops him.   \n\nWhen Tony goes out on the day, [[Christopher Moltisanti|Chris]], who is concerned about his boss's emotional state, secretly follows him and  unknowingly prevents the hit when he pulls his car up next to the assassins'. There is an urgent outdoor meeting between Mikey and Donnie; Junior is present, hiding on the back seat of the car. Donnie promises the hit will be the next day, and casually remarks that even Tony's mother wants him dead. Junior, fearing the gossip, wordlessly tells Mikey to kill Donnie, and he does it. \n\nThe next day, the assassins make their move. In a ferocious struggle, one of them is killed and the other is briefly dragged along the street as Tony drives away. Elated, he can't help crashing into a parked car. In the hospital, with only minor injuries, he says it was an attempted carjack, but not even [[Anthony Soprano, Jr.|A.J.]] believes that. [[Federal Bureau of Investigation|FBI]] Agent [[Dwight Harris|Harris]] comes to his bed and offers a deal, including [[immunity from prosecution]], which Tony scornfully rejects.\n\nThe next day, Livia and Junior call on Tony at home. Livia apparently cannot recognize her granddaughter; Junior comments on the \"good timing\" of this memory loss.\n\n==Deceased==\n* '''[[List of characters from The Sopranos in the Soprano crime family#Donnie Paduana|Donnie Paduana]]:''' murdered by [[Mikey Palmice]] on orders of Uncle Junior.\n* '''[[List of characters from The Sopranos in the Soprano crime family#William \"Petite\" Clayborn|William \"Petite\" Clayborn]]:''' accidentally shot by his partner, Rasheen Ray, in the failed attempt on Tony Soprano's life.\n\n==Title reference==\nIsabella is the Italia